Voters in Bauchi  are going to elect 31 out of 368 House of Assembly candidates and one out of 31 governorship candidates across various political parties. Bauchi State has 31 constituencies in the House ‎of Assembly. INEC, Head of Voter Education and Publicity, Ahmed Waziri Zadawa confirmed the number of candidates while addressing journalists at the INEC office in Bauchi. He therefore called on all eligible voters to come out and vote for the candidate of their choice adding that INEC has prepared to conduct a free, fair and credible election. 32 jostle for Gombe governorship, 253 for assembly seats 31 governorship, 371 State Assembly candidates for March 9 elections in Niger Poll readiness: Domestic observers laud Bauchi INEC, parties, security agencies